WEBVTT

00:00,000 --> 00:02,950
The useful signal in A practical leadership workflow for data and analytics that teams will use 03040530 is how decisions are run when pressure is high.

00:03,000 --> 00:05,950
Because practical is easier to produce now, teams can mistake volume for progress. Last week in the weekly operations standup, the blocker was not motivation.

00:06,000 --> 00:08,950
Problem one: teams collect more inputs, but weak checkpoints keep outcomes flat.

00:09,000 --> 00:11,950
So run one compact loop: brief, prototype, test with a small audience, then review evidence.

00:12,000 --> 00:14,950
Then ship in a short sprint so feedback stays close to live work.

00:15,000 --> 00:17,950
Problem two: performance support breaks when roles and expectations keep mutating.

00:18,000 --> 00:20,950
So where does data fit when business transformation, not content volume, is the main game?

00:21,000 --> 00:29,950
What do you think?
